The following companies may have
unusual price changes in  Spain  and  Portugal  trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  fell 1.5 percent to 10,622.70.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  fell 1.6 percent to 7,759.50.  Spanish stocks:  Corporacion Financiera Alba SA (ALB SM): The financial
holding company said it will pay an extraordinary dividend of 3
euros per share. The shares gained 0.1 percent to 43.02 euros.  Portuguese stocks:  Impresa SGPS SA (IPR)  : Ongoing Strategy Investments SGPS
SA, a Portuguese investment company, is considering whether to
keep its stake in the TV broadcaster and publisher, Ongoing
Chairman Nuno Vasconcellos said in a telephone interview.
Impresa dropped 1 percent to 99 euro cents.  To contact the reporter on this story: Emma Ross-Thomas in
Madrid   erossthomas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
